      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you with that. I will modify your code to optimize the search for the longest palindromic substring. This will significantly reduce the runtime, especially for large strings.\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(n):\n        # Odd length palindromes\n        l, r = i, i\n        while l >= 0 and r < n and s[l] == s[r]:\n            if (r - l + 1) > len(res):\n                res = s[l:r+1]\n            l -= 1\n            r += 1\n        # Even length palindromes\n        l, r = i, i + 1\n        while l >= 0 and r < n and s[l] == s[r]:\n            if (r - l + 1) > len(res):\n                res = s[l:r+1]\n            l -= 1\n            r += 1\n    return res\n```\n\nThis optimized code uses a two-pointer technique to find both odd and even length palindromes efficiently. It should pass the autograder's runtime check for large inputs.",
