      "content": "I will introduce a heuristic to quickly estimate the longest palindromic substring without processing the entire string. This heuristic will be based on the assumption that the longest palindromic substring is likely to be centered around the middle of the string, and it will only process a smaller portion of the string.\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    if n < 2:\n        return s\n\n    def expand_around_center(left, right):\n        while left >= 0 and right < n and s[left] == s[right]:\n            left -= 1\n            right += 1\n        return s[left + 1:right]\n\n    res = \"\"\n    mid = n // 2\n    for i in range(mid + 1):\n        odd = expand_around_center(i, i)\n        even = expand_around_center(i, i + 1)\n        if len(odd) > len(res):\n            res = odd\n        if len(even) > len(res):\n            res = even\n\n    return res\n```\n\nThis code uses a heuristic to quickly estimate the longest palindromic substring by expanding around the center of the string. This should significantly reduce the processing time",
